{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":940,"text":"Five years ago, I had my dream job."},{"time":4653,"text":"I was a foreign correspondent\nin the Middle East"},{"time":7081,"text":"reporting for ABC News."},{"time":9245,"text":"But there was a crack in the wall,"},{"time":11333,"text":"a problem with our industry,"},{"time":13739,"text":"that I felt we needed to fix."},{"time":16581,"text":"You see, I got to the Middle East\nright around the end of 2007,"},{"time":20746,"text":"which was just around the midpoint"},{"time":23027,"text":"of the Iraq War."},{"time":24751,"text":"But by the time I got there,\nit was already nearly impossible"},{"time":28224,"text":"to find stories about Iraq on air."},{"time":31525,"text":"Coverage had dropped across the board,"},{"time":33799,"text":"across networks."},{"time":35136,"text":"And of the stories that did make it,"},{"time":37216,"text":"more than 80 percent\nof them were about us."},{"time":40561,"text":"We were missing the stories about Iraq,"},{"time":43138,"text":"the people who live there,"},{"time":45255,"text":"and what was happening to them\nunder the weight of the war."}]},{"cues":[{"time":49054,"text":"Afghanistan had already\nfallen off the agenda."},{"time":52834,"text":"There were less than one percent\nof all news stories in 2008"},{"time":56499,"text":"that went to the war in Afghanistan."},{"time":58762,"text":"It was the longest war in US history,"},{"time":61729,"text":"but information was so scarce"},{"time":63715,"text":"that schoolteachers we spoke to"},{"time":65974,"text":"told us they had trouble\nexplaining to their students"},{"time":69125,"text":"what we were doing there,"},{"time":70689,"text":"when those students had parents"},{"time":72610,"text":"who were fighting\nand sometimes dying overseas."}]},{"cues":[{"time":77177,"text":"We had drawn a blank,"},{"time":78865,"text":"and it wasn't just Iraq and Afghanistan."},{"time":81671,"text":"From conflict zones to climate change"},{"time":84368,"text":"to all sorts of issues\naround crises in public health,"},{"time":88678,"text":"we were missing what I call\nthe species-level issues,"},{"time":92098,"text":"because as a species,\nthey could actually sink us."},{"time":95664,"text":"And by failing to understand\nthe complex issues of our time,"},{"time":100407,"text":"we were facing certain\npractical implications."},{"time":103765,"text":"How were we going to solve problems"},{"time":105541,"text":"that we didn't fundamentally understand,"},{"time":107836,"text":"that we couldn't track in real time,"},{"time":110124,"text":"and where the people working on the issues"},{"time":112462,"text":"were invisible to us"},{"time":113829,"text":"and sometimes invisible to each other?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":117640,"text":"When you look back on Iraq,"},{"time":119648,"text":"those years when we\nwere missing the story,"},{"time":123101,"text":"were the years when the society\nwas falling apart,"},{"time":125887,"text":"when we were setting the conditions\nfor what would become the rise of ISIS,"},{"time":129846,"text":"the ISIS takeover of Mosul"},{"time":132032,"text":"and terrorist violence that would spread"},{"time":134099,"text":"beyond Iraq's borders\nto the rest of the world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":137757,"text":"Just around that time\nwhere I was making that observation,"},{"time":141088,"text":"I looked across the border of Iraq"},{"time":142954,"text":"and noticed there was another\nstory we were missing:"},{"time":146017,"text":"the war in Syria."},{"time":147573,"text":"If you were a Middle-East specialist,\nyou knew that Syria was that important"},{"time":152313,"text":"from the start."},{"time":153582,"text":"But it ended up being, really,"},{"time":155146,"text":"one of the forgotten stories\nof the Arab Spring."},{"time":158846,"text":"I saw the implications up front."},{"time":162244,"text":"Syria is intimately tied\nto regional security,"},{"time":165635,"text":"to global stability."},{"time":167606,"text":"I felt like we couldn't let that become"},{"time":169519,"text":"another one of the stories we left behind."}]},{"cues":[{"time":172502,"text":"So I left my big TV job to start\na website, called \"Syria Deeply.\""},{"time":178305,"text":"It was designed to be a news\nand information source"},{"time":181079,"text":"that made it easier to understand\na complex issue,"},{"time":184452,"text":"and for the past four years,\nit's been a resource"},{"time":186845,"text":"for policymakers and professionals\nworking on the conflict in Syria."},{"time":191940,"text":"We built a business model"},{"time":193387,"text":"based on consistent,\nhigh-quality information,"},{"time":196666,"text":"and convening the top minds on the issue."},{"time":200407,"text":"And we found it was a model that scaled."},{"time":203271,"text":"We got passionate requests\nto do other things \"Deeply.\""},{"time":207075,"text":"So we started to work our way\ndown the list."}]},{"cues":[{"time":211167,"text":"I'm just one of many entrepreneurs,"},{"time":214193,"text":"and we are just one of many start-ups"},{"time":216799,"text":"trying to fix what's wrong with news."},{"time":219684,"text":"All of us in the trenches know"},{"time":221654,"text":"that something is wrong\nwith the news industry."},{"time":224153,"text":"It's broken."},{"time":226556,"text":"Trust in the media\nhas hit an all-time low."},{"time":229927,"text":"And the statistic you're seeing up there\nis from September --"},{"time":233346,"text":"it's arguably gotten worse."},{"time":236104,"text":"But we can fix this."},{"time":237600,"text":"We can fix the news."},{"time":240263,"text":"I know that that's true."},{"time":242106,"text":"You can call me an idealist;\nI call myself an industrious optimist."},{"time":247419,"text":"And I know there are\na lot of us out there."},{"time":249968,"text":"We have ideas for how\nto make things better,"},{"time":252384,"text":"and I want to share three of them\nthat we've picked up in our own work."}]},{"cues":[{"time":256848,"text":"Idea number one:"},{"time":258661,"text":"we need news that's built\non deep-domain knowledge."},{"time":262348,"text":"Given the waves and waves of layoffs\nat newsrooms across the country,"},{"time":266130,"text":"we've lost the art of specialization."},{"time":268432,"text":"Beat reporting is an endangered thing."},{"time":271139,"text":"When it comes to foreign news,"},{"time":273410,"text":"the way we can fix that\nis by working with more local journalists,"},{"time":276595,"text":"treating them like our partners\nand collaborators,"},{"time":279000,"text":"not just fixers who fetch us\nphone numbers and sound bites."},{"time":282867,"text":"Our local reporters in Syria\nand across Africa and across Asia"},{"time":287107,"text":"bring us stories that we certainly\nwould not have found on our own."},{"time":291118,"text":"Like this one from the suburbs\nof Damascus, about a wheelchair race"},{"time":295358,"text":"that gave hope\nto those wounded in the war."},{"time":298243,"text":"Or this one from Sierra Leone,"},{"time":300140,"text":"about a local chief\nwho curbed the spread of Ebola"},{"time":303621,"text":"by self-organizing\na quarantine in his district."},{"time":307526,"text":"Or this one from the border of Pakistan,"},{"time":309676,"text":"about Afghan refugees being forced\nto return home before they are ready,"},{"time":313629,"text":"under the threat of police intimidation."},{"time":316705,"text":"Our local journalists are our mentors."},{"time":318783,"text":"They teach us something new every day,"},{"time":320909,"text":"and they bring us stories\nthat are important for all of us to know."}]},{"cues":[{"time":325630,"text":"Idea number two:"},{"time":327448,"text":"we need a kind of Hippocratic oath\nfor the news industry,"},{"time":331111,"text":"a pledge to first do no harm."}]},{"cues":[{"time":334738,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":336373,"text":"Journalists need to be tough."},{"time":337915,"text":"We need to speak truth to power,"},{"time":339851,"text":"but we also need to be responsible."},{"time":341976,"text":"We need to live up to our own ideals,"},{"time":344344,"text":"and we need to recognize"},{"time":346299,"text":"when what we're doing\ncould potentially harm society,"},{"time":350212,"text":"where we lose track of journalism\nas a public service."}]},{"cues":[{"time":354353,"text":"I watched us cover the Ebola crisis."},{"time":356352,"text":"We launched Ebola Deeply. We did our best."},{"time":358772,"text":"But what we saw was a public"},{"time":360702,"text":"that was flooded with hysterical\nand sensational coverage,"},{"time":364343,"text":"sometimes inaccurate,\nsometimes completely wrong."},{"time":367512,"text":"Public health experts tell me\nthat that actually cost us in human lives,"},{"time":372164,"text":"because by sparking more panic\nand by sometimes getting the facts wrong,"},{"time":376861,"text":"we made it harder for people to resolve"},{"time":379057,"text":"what was actually happening on the ground."},{"time":381151,"text":"All that noise made it harder\nto make the right decisions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":385060,"text":"We can do better as an industry,"},{"time":387261,"text":"but it requires us recognizing\nhow we got it wrong last time,"},{"time":391650,"text":"and deciding not to go that way next time."},{"time":395021,"text":"It's a choice."},{"time":396261,"text":"We have to resist the temptation\nto use fear for ratings."},{"time":400583,"text":"And that decision has to be made\nin the individual newsroom"},{"time":403514,"text":"and with the individual news executive."},{"time":405709,"text":"Because the next deadly virus\nthat comes around"},{"time":408388,"text":"could be much worse\nand the consequences much higher,"},{"time":412193,"text":"if we do what we did last time;"},{"time":414152,"text":"if our reporting isn't responsible\nand it isn't right."}]},{"cues":[{"time":419192,"text":"The third idea?"},{"time":420767,"text":"We need to embrace complexity"},{"time":422922,"text":"if we want to make sense\nof a complex world."},{"time":426136,"text":"Embrace complexity --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":428042,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":429543,"text":"not treat the world simplistically,\nbecause simple isn't accurate."},{"time":434938,"text":"We live in a complex world."},{"time":437461,"text":"News is adult education."},{"time":439445,"text":"It's our job as journalists\nto get elbow deep in complexity"},{"time":442924,"text":"and to find new ways to make it easier\nfor everyone else to understand."},{"time":447627,"text":"If we don't do that,"},{"time":448820,"text":"if we pretend there are\njust simple answers,"},{"time":451654,"text":"we're leading everyone off a steep cliff."},{"time":455324,"text":"Understanding complexity\nis the only way to know the real threats"},{"time":458799,"text":"that are around the corner."},{"time":460156,"text":"It's our responsibility\nto translate those threats"},{"time":462885,"text":"and to help you understand what's real,"},{"time":465094,"text":"so you can be prepared and know\nwhat it takes to be ready"},{"time":468351,"text":"for what comes next."}]},{"cues":[{"time":471005,"text":"I am an industrious optimist."},{"time":472586,"text":"I do believe we can fix what's broken."},{"time":475678,"text":"We all want to."},{"time":476885,"text":"There are great journalists\nout there doing great work --"},{"time":479693,"text":"we just need new formats."},{"time":482042,"text":"I honestly believe\nthis is a time of reawakening,"},{"time":485787,"text":"reimagining what we can do."},{"time":488079,"text":"I believe we can fix what's broken."},{"time":490616,"text":"I know we can fix the news."},{"time":492572,"text":"I know it's worth trying,"},{"time":494422,"text":"and I truly believe that in the end,"},{"time":496589,"text":"we're going to get this right."}]},{"cues":[{"time":498231,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":499423,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}